From ee70efc9586dbdd56cadf121a0bee0183949085e Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date: Sun, 21 Jun 2026 00:02:09 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Migrate auth to Supabase Auth, add self-service profile UI,
 tighten RLS

Fixes the "invalid input syntax for type uuid" bug by replacing the
custom app_users/RPC + localStorage session model with real Supabase
Auth sessions (no more trusting unvalidated cached client state).

Adds a profile dialog (name update, email change with confirmation
link, password reset via emailed OTP) wired into the user menu, backed
by new auth-context methods and Supabase's built-in auth emails.

Tightens previously fully-open RLS policies (USING(true)/WITH
CHECK(true)) on items/transactions/transaction_items/settings/item_history
to require authentication, with admin-only writes on items/settings,
and locks down trigger-only SECURITY DEFINER function grants.
